    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n9691" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χρέος, χρεῖος</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χράομαι</span>): (1) <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">want, need</span>, then
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">affair, business</span>, <i><span class="en">Od.
            1.409</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 2.45</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; Τειρεσίᾱο κατὰ χρέος</span>, for
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">want</span> of T., i. e. to consult him, <i><span class="en">Od. 11.479</span></i>.—(2) what one must pay,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">debt</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὀφείλειν τινί, ὀφέλλεταί
            μοι</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 11.688</span></i>,
          686.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
